" lines starting with a double quote are comments.
"
" how to use this file:
" 1. install this file into the home folder of your CS account.
" 2. cp myvimrc $HOME/.vimrc
" 3. use vim wherever you have C source files to edit.
"
" what this file does:
" a. shows line numbering
" b. fills tab characters with space characters instead
" c. auto-indents based on input of curly braces
" d. uses a 4 space per indentation model of block layout
" e. highlights matching curly braces and brackets
" f. colors syntax based on C and other language code
"
" Note: uncommented, these colorschemes can do things like dark mode:
" colorscheme desert
" colorscheme morning
set number
syntax on
" auto indent tabstop=4 fill with spaces
set autoindent
set smartindent
set smarttab
set expandtab
set tabstop=4
set shiftwidth=4
set softtabstop=4
" showmatching braces, etc
set showmatch
set backspace=indent,eol,start
set winminheight=0
set winminwidth=0
set ruler

